{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"fd4b974f-41c4-44c3-9046-324f334f3e9b","content":"\n\nIn .NET MAUI, use the **lifecycle events API** in `MauiProgram.cs` (or your app builder setup):\n\n```csharp\nbuilder.ConfigureLifecycleEvents(events =>\n{\n#if ANDROID\n    events.AddAndroid(android => android\n        .OnPause(activity => { /* your code */ })\n        .OnStop(activity => { /* your code */ }));\n#endif\n\n#if IOS\n    events.AddiOS(ios => ios\n        .DidEnterBackground(app => { /* your code */ }));\n#endif\n});\n```\n\n**Key points:**\n\n- Add `using Microsoft.Maui.LifecycleEvents;` at the top.\n- Platform-specific blocks are guarded with `#if` directives so they only compile on the target platform.\n- Other events are available too (e.g., `OnResume`, `WillEnterForeground`, `OnCreate`, etc.).\n- Alternatively, you can override lifecycle methods directly in a custom `MauiAppCompatActivity` (Android) or `AppDelegate` (iOS) if you prefer platform project-level hooks.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"11fba8a0-96ba-4fd6-af61-98efc336efe5","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about how to hook into platform-specific lifecycle events in .NET MAUI — specifically Android's `OnPause`/`OnStop` and iOS's `DidEnterBackground`. This is a general knowledge question, not a code task.","outputTokens":343},"id":"2228d326-2a53-4e25-954b-b2ddda5a9663","timestamp":"2026-04-03T00:47:42.840Z","parentId":"54c7e631-ce80-495c-a46f-753488186b01"}
